{"id":1316829145,"question_id":3491,"lang":"cpp","lang_name":"C++","time":"2 weeks, 2 days","timestamp":1720640376,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"89 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1316829145/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Find the Maximum Length of Valid Subsequence II","memory":"30.2 MB","code":"class Solution {\npublic:\n    int maximumLength(vector<int>& nums, int k) {\n        int f[k][k];\n        memset(f, 0, sizeof(f));\n        int ans = 0;\n        for (int x : nums) {\n            x %= k;\n            for (int j = 0; j < k; ++j) {\n                int y = (j - x + k) % k;\n                f[x][y] = f[y][x] + 1;\n                ans = max(ans, f[x][y]);\n            }\n        }\n        return ans;\n    }\n};","compare_result":"","title_slug":"find-the-maximum-length-of-valid-subsequence-ii","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
